        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 3 at 8:32PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 831 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from near Scipio to 2 miles southeast of Ashland.
Movement was northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts 40 to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.

Locations in or near the path include...
Arpelar...                        Kiowa...
Haywood...                        Scipio...
Ashland...                        Mcalester...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for southeastern
Oklahoma.</instruction>
